        <p style="transform:translateY(90px) translateX(1px);font-size: 19px;">When you set foot on Saigon, it's a crime not to visit one of the icons of the city — the Bitexco Financial Tower. Standing 262 metres, 68 floors tall, Bitexco Financial Tower is Vietnam's first and truly International Standard Grade A building. Inspired by the lotus, Vietnam's national flower, this urban icon evokes beauty, progress and Vietnam's huge potential and global aspirations.     </p>
        <p style="transform:translateY(100px) translateX(1px);font-size: 19px;">Since its opening in 2011, this tower welcomes thousands of guests per year, thanks to its observation deck named Saigon Skydeck on the 49th floor. With an amazing panoramic view of the city, this is one destination you don't want to miss.    </p>
        <p style="transform:translateY(110px) translateX(1px);font-size: 19px;">On top of the spectacular view, a trip to Saigon Skydeck also gives you an exclusive look into the Ao Dai Exhibition—a cooperation with The Southern Women Museum which displays and introduces a variety of beautiful Ao Dai over times and helps to preserve and promote the unique Vietnamese cultural heritage to visitors.    </p>
        <p style="transform:translateY(120px) translateX(1px);font-size: 19px;">Photo ops are plentiful, and the spectacular backdrop of the city provides an ultimate setting for your lunch or dinner at the deck's restaurant if you so choose.    </p>
